description:
Métis N4 Construction Inc. is the fastest growing 100% Indigenous owned and operated development and project management company in Manitoba. The corporation was established in 2014 to provide the MMF, the National Government of the Red River Métis, with a vehicle to pursue effective Red River Métis participation in economic and major resource development projects. Working as the Owner’s Project Manager, Métis N4 leads a diverse portfolio valued over $150M.


Métis N4 seeks to fill **one full\-time Project Manager** position located at **150 Henry Avenue** in **Winnipeg, MB**. The Project Manager is responsible for leading and delivering construction and development projects on behalf of the owner, from early planning stages through to completion.

***Job Duties/Competencies:***

* Maintain a positive and solutions\-oriented approach to work;
* Provide project management services on behalf of the owner from pre\-development to close\-out;
* Facilitate and document owner project requirements;
* Conduct site inspections during construction as the Owner’s Project Manager;
* Attend meetings, produce minutes, and coordinate follow\-up actions and deliverables as required;
* Provide project Contract Administration: review progress billing submissions for completeness and accuracy;
* Review and summarize project estimates, bids, budgets and quotations;
* Produce project documents such as: RFP, RFQ, EOI;
* Assist in tracking and reporting on construction labour hours and Red River Métis labour hours;
* Develop risk management analysis and critical path documentation.
***Skills and Qualifications:***

* Post\-Secondary education in Project Management, Engineering, B.EnvD. or Planning;
* Minimum two (2\) years of applied project management in the fields of: construction, engineering, architecture,

or real estate development;

* Proficient in Microsoft Office: Word, Excel, OneDrive, PowerPoint, Outlook;
* Strong organizational, interpersonal and time management skills;
* Acceptable Criminal Record Check with a Vulnerable Sector Search and Adult Abuse Registry Check is required;
* Knowledge of Red River Métis Government and culture is an asset; and,
* Ability to travel, valid Manitoba Driver’s license with access to a reliable vehicle.

We offer a comprehensive benefits package including; health, dental, vision, pension, and vacation.

**Please submit your resume and cover letter, referencing the job posting number by Wednesday, April 1, 2026\.**


N4 is committed to providing an inclusive and accessible recruitment process. If you require accommodation during any stage of the recruitment process, please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.

**N4 requires satisfactory background checks prior to commencement of employment. N4 will accept existing background checks if dated within 3 months of your start date. Obtaining these documents is not a guarantee of employment.**


Preference will be given to qualified Red River Métis applicants and they are encouraged to self\-identify on their cover letter. The MMF encourages internal applicants to apply for career opportunities within our Government.

Métis N4 Construction Inc. is the fastest growing 100% Indigenous owned and operated development and project management company in Manitoba. The corporation was established in 2014 to provide the MMF, the National Government of the Red River Métis, with a vehicle to pursue effective Red River Métis participation in economic and major resource development projects.


Métis N4 seeks to fill **one full\-time Project Coordinator** position located at **150 Henry Avenue** in **Winnipeg, MB**. The Project Coordinator will be responsible for coordinating project logistics, maintaining documentation, supporting procurement and financial tracking, and ensuring effective communication among stakeholders.

***Job Duties/Competencies:***

* Coordinate day\-to\-day project activities to ensure alignment with schedules, budgets, and scope;
* Support general administrative functions related to project delivery;
* Assist in Finance related items such as invoice tracking, cost monitoring, billing submissions etc;
* Assist in developing Owner Project Requirements and project plans;
* Track project milestones, deliverables, and critical path activities;
* Coordinate procurement of materials, appliances, furnishings, and fit\-up requirements;
* Conduct site visits to monitor progress, document conditions, and identify issues;
* Photograph and document construction progress and site conditions;
* Assist in reviewing estimates, bids, budgets, and quotations and provide summarized recommendations;
* Conduct research on materials, industry trends, and supply chain considerations.
***Skills and Qualifications:***

* Post\-Secondary education in Construction Management, Project Management, Engineering, Architecture, Business Administration, or a related field;
* Minimum 3 years’ of experience in project coordination, construction, or a related field;
* Experience with Project Management Software and/or MS Office is an asset;
* Proven ability to problem solve with the ability to adapt to changing priorities;
* Strong communication, organizational, interpersonal and time management skills;
* Acceptable Criminal Record Check is required;
* Knowledge of Red River Métis Government and culture is an asset; and,
* Ability to travel, valid Manitoba Driver’s license with access to a reliable vehicle.

We offer a comprehensive benefits package including; health, dental, vision, pension, and vacation.

**Please submit your resume and cover letter, referencing the job posting number by Wednesday, April 1, 2026\.**


N4 is committed to providing an inclusive and accessible recruitment process. If you require accommodation during any stage of the recruitment process, please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.

**N4 requires satisfactory background checks prior to commencement of employment. N4 will accept existing background checks if dated within 3 months of your start date. Obtaining these documents is not a guarantee of employment.**


Preference will be given to qualified Red River Métis applicants and they are encouraged to self\-identify on their cover letter. The MMF encourages internal applicants to apply for career opportunities within our Government.

The Manitoba Métis Federation (MMF) is the democratically elected National Government of the Red River Métis, also known as the Manitoba Métis. The Red River Métis are a distinct Indigenous Nation and People, and Canada's Negotiating Partners in Confederation and the Founders of the Province of Manitoba.


The MMF seeks to fill **one full\-time Research Associate** position within our **Housing Department** located at 150 Henry Avenue in **Winnipeg, MB**. The Research Associate will conduct comprehensive research, analyze data, identify service gaps, and contribute to policy development. The Research Associate will collaborate with external stakeholders, coordinate projects, and generate reports to inform and improve homelessness programming.

***Job Duties/Competencies:***

* In collaboration with the MMF’s Departments, arrange and facilitate individual and group consultations;
* Collect and prepare quantitative and qualitative data for analysis;
* Develop a database to effectively and efficiently store and retrieve data;
* Draft articles, reports, and presentations regarding research findings;
* Find and present funding opportunities for programming and supports to Program Manager;
* Facilitate research and analysis of housing issues to help assist in identifying their implications as they relate to the adaptation of programs and services;
* Collect, compile and present comprehensive reports for research conducted and suggested policy;
* Perform a range of administrative tasks with respect to the full research cycle and assist with writing for the Housing Dept.
***Skills and Qualifications:***

* Degree in Social Science, Social Services, or relevant field, and/or equivalent experience may be considered;
* Two years’ experience with quantitative/qualitative and community\-based research methods;
* Extensive experience working with at\-risk/vulnerable population;
* Experience in report writing and proposal development;
* Experience with research software procedures and best practices;
* Proficiency in Microsoft Office: Word, Excel, Outlook, and PowerPoint;
* Acceptable Criminal Record Check with a Vulnerable Sector Search is required;
* Experience working for a not\-for\-profit organization and Indigenous community is an asset;
* Knowledge of Red River Métis culture, MMF programs and services is a definite asset; and,
* Ability to travel, valid Manitoba Driver’s license with access to a reliable vehicle.

We offer a comprehensive benefits package including; health, dental, vision, pension, and vacation.

**Please submit your resume and cover letter, referencing the job posting number by Sunday, April 5, 2026\.**


The MMF is committed to providing an inclusive and accessible recruitment process. If you require accommodation during any stage of the recruitment process, please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.

**The MMF requires satisfactory background checks prior to commencement of employment. The MMF will accept existing background checks if dated within 3 months of your start date. Obtaining these documents is not a guarantee of employment.**


Preference will be given to qualified Red River Métis applicants and they are encouraged to self\-identify on their cover letter. The MMF encourages internal applicants to apply for career opportunities within our Government.
